OpenCut for Linux (opencut-linux)
=================================

This is an UNOFFICIAL, community-maintained Linux desktop package (.deb) of
OpenCut. It is not produced, endorsed by, or affiliated with the OpenCut
project or its authors.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Upstream software
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This package bundles and redistributes OpenCut (the archived "classic"
codebase), a free and open source video editor.

    OpenCut
    Copyright (c) 2025-2026 OpenCut
    License: MIT (see licenses/OpenCut-LICENSE)
    Upstream: https://github.com/opencut-app/opencut-classic
    Active rewrite: https://github.com/opencut-app/opencut

The full, unmodified OpenCut MIT license text is preserved in:
    licenses/OpenCut-LICENSE

Small source patches applied to make an offline desktop build are documented in
patches/opencut-classic-fixes.patch and are described in the README. They do not
change the license of the upstream code.

